'''Hematuria''' is the presence of [[blood]] in the urine. It may have a benign cause, but in some cases can be caused by an illness that could cause [[death]].  
==Causes==
*[[Renal cell carcinoma]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/kidney-cancer/DS00360/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Cystitis]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/cystitis/DS00285/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Bladder cancer]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/bladder-cancer/DS00177/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Pyelonephritis]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/kidney-infection/DS00593/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Prostate cancer]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/prostate-cancer/DS00043/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Urethritis]]<ref>http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/000439.htm</ref>
*[[Wilms tumor]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/wilms-tumor/DS00436/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*[[Kidney stones]]<ref>http://kidney.niddk.nih.gov/kudiseases/pubs/stones_ez/</ref>
*[[Glomerulonephritis]]<ref>http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/glomerulonephritis/DS00503/DSECTION=symptoms</ref>
*Possibly, [[allergies]]. <ref>http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12425491</ref>
